  "prompt": "Why do Yaz birth control pills cause weight loss?",
  "response": "Yaz birth control pills do not actually cause weight loss. In fact, some women may experience slight weight gain as a side effect. The misconception about weight loss might stem from individual experiences or marketing claims. \n\nHere are some key points about Yaz and weight:\n\n1. Hormonal changes can affect weight in different ways for different women.\n\n2. Some women might experience water retention or bloating when starting birth control.\n\n3. Yaz contains drospirenone, a progestin that may have mild diuretic effects, which could lead to temporary water weight loss.\n\n4. Individual metabolism and lifestyle factors play a more significant role in weight changes.\n\nIf you're concerned about weight changes while on birth control, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional who can provide personalized advice.",
